{{Infobox book | name = Encyclopedia of Christianity | title_orig = | translator = | image = Encyclopedia of Christianity.jpg | caption = | author = [[John Stephen Bowden]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = English | series = | subject = [[Christianity]] | genre = | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | pub_date = August 2005 | media_type = Print | pages = 1364 | isbn = 0195223934 | dewey = 230.003 | congress = BR95 .E47 2005 | oclc = 60359641 }} The '''''Encyclopedia of Christianity''''' is a one-volume [[encyclopedia]] published by [[Oxford University Press]] and edited by [[John Bowden (theologian)|John Bowden]] of the [[University of Nottingham]] and [[King's College, London]].<ref name = thechristiancentury>[http://www.christiancentury.org/reviews/2006-10/encyclopedia-christianity The Christian Century - Review]</ref><ref name = Ostling>[[Richard N. Ostling]], [http://azdailysun.com/two-reference-works-rank-as-s-best-books-on-religion/article_0ed720f2-b580-56b6-b3fe-beb7bf001d2a.html "Two reference works rank as 2005's best books on religion"], [[Associated Press]] in ''[[Arizona Daily Sun]]'', December 9, 2005.</ref> It contains over three hundred articles on a variety of [[Christian]] topics and themes.<ref name="Bowden2005">{{cite book|author=John Stephen Bowden|title=Encyclopedia of Christianity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NGAUAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=23 April 2013|date=15 August 2005|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-522393-4}}</ref> Some of the authors include professor [[John Barton (theologian)|John Barton]] from [[Oxford University]], [[Cynthia B. Cohen]] from [[Georgetown University]] and [[Martin Marty]] from the [[University of Chicago]]. It contains twenty one color pictures and ninety six black and white [[illustration]]s.<ref name = pubweekly>[http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-19-522393-4 Publishers Weekly - Review]</ref><ref>Douglas A Sweeney. "Books Reviews and Notes". [[Church History (periodical)|Church History]]. Vol 75. Issue 4. December 2006. pp 961 - 962. [http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract;jsessionid=E97C5A52DD5E129282657369C3E97AA7.journals?fromPage=online&aid=2307504 Cambridge Journals].</ref>
In his introduction Bowden noted that most Christians have only a limited understanding of the traditions of their own religion.<ref name = Ostling/> ''[[The Christian Century]]'' called the encyclopedia "a major scholarly achievement" but noted that it relied entirely on scholars from Europe and North America.<ref name = thechristiancentury/> Religion writer [[Richard Ostling]] called this book, together with its companion release, the ''Oxford Dictionary of the Christian Church'' (3rd ed.), "2005's books of the year in religion", and commented that the ''Encyclopedia'' takes a "relatively moderate approach to literary and historical disputes."<ref name = Ostling/> ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' said: "Overall, this encyclopedia is a must-have for any Christian reference shelf." <ref name = pubweekly/>
