{| class="toccolours" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; width: 21em; font-size: 90%; clear: right;" cellspacing="5" |- |+ style="text-align: center; font-size: larger; margin-left: inherit;" | '''Japanese-Lithuanian Hieroglyphs Dictionary''' |- |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Original Title (Lithuanian)''' | Japonų-lietuvių kalbų hieroglifų žodynas |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Author(s)''' | Dalia Švambarytė |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Genre''' | [[Dictionary]] |- | colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-size: larger;" | '''Data''' |- style="vertical-align: top;" |'''Released''' | 2002 |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Publisher''' | Alma Littera |- style="vertical-align: top;" |'''Pages''' | 792 |- style="vertical-align: top;" |'''ISBN''' | {{ISBNT|9955-08-130-9}} |}
'''''Japanese-Lithuanian Hieroglyphs Dictionary''''' ({{lang-lt|Japonų-lietuvių kalbų hieroglifų žodynas}}, {{lang-ja|漢リ字典}}) is the [[Japanese language|Japanese]]-[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]] dictionary. It is the only Japanese–Lithuanian dictionary that has been published in [[Lithuania]]. Author – [[habilitation|hab. dr.]] Dalia Švambarytė.
In the dictionary, there are total 3763 [[kanji]].
